OL,6,F"The statistics and the figures back
OL,7,Fthat up; a woman is more likely to be
OL,8,Fmurdered by their son at 10%, than the
OL,9,F9% of women who are murdered by
OL,10,Fstrangers.
OL,12,F"94% of women who are murdered by men
OL,13,Finvolved some element of stalking
OL,14,Fbehaviour, and 71% of those women were
OL,15,Fin, or had been in, a relationship
OL,16,Fwith the person who killed them."
OL,18,FIn July, a 45-year-old mother and her
OL,19,Fchildren were shot at their home on
OL,20,FMaguiresbridge.
